                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18450818-name-412" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18450818-name-412" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450818-name-412" type="surname" value="BRADLEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450818-name-412" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS BRADLEY</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">City police-constable, No.</hi> 269.) On the night of the 27th of July, at a quarter before twelve o'clock, I was on Holborn-hill—I saw the prisoner, and four or five others with him, following a gen<lb></lb>tleman—I saw the prisoner lift the tail of the gentleman's coat with his left hand, put his right hand into his pocket, and take a handkerchief out—I took him, and he threw the handkerchief away—I do not know who the gentleman was.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> How far was you away from me? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Eleven or twelve yards—I took you directly—the other officer, who was with me, scrambled after the handkerchief amongst the others, and whilst he did that the gen<lb></lb>tleman was gone.</p>
               <p>
